headline: DaVita’s Q2 Earnings Call: Our Top 5 Analyst Questions
summary: DaVita’s second quarter was met with a significant negative market reaction, as shares declined sharply despite management delivering results that surpassed Wall Street’s expectations for revenue and adjusted profit. The quarter was marked by two main operational challenges: a decline in treatment volumes and lingering effects from a major cyberattack earlier in the year. headline: DVA Q2 Deep Dive: Cyber Incident Drives Volume Headwinds as Cost Controls Support Outlook
summary: Dialysis provider DaVita Inc. (NYSE:DVA) reported Q2 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 6.1% year on year to $3.38 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.95 per share was 7.3% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
